The paper deals with a novel linear receiver architecture called Integer Forcing (IF) that is used for decoding multiple transmissions in wireless communication systems. This falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the practical implementation of IF, which involves block-based decoding schemes, and the evaluation of the effective SNR distribution. This could fall under the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and complexity analysis, which could fall under the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. The simulations and performance evaluation could fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves theoretical analysis and bounds, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
